Other guidelines intended to assist practitioners where an opposing party is self-represented include “Guidelines for Solicitors Dealing with Self-represented Parties” (April 2006) at the NSW Law Society website (
http://www.lawsociety.com.au/idc/groups/public/documents/internet costguidebook/008731.pdf
) and “Guidelines for barristers on dealing with self-represented litigants” (October 2001) at NSW Bar Association website (
http://www.nswbar.asn.au/docs/resources/ publications/self_reps_14112011.pdf
).

